snippet.textDisplay:
Shalom Aleichem



I'am Daniel Moshe Johnson, I signed the first NBA contract with an organization I will not name at this present time.



I loved Kobe Bryant's approach to the game, ethics, commitment and winning spirit.


Because of deceit, lying, under handed dealings, my life was devastated, and I died, like Kobe, Gigi, Payton Chester, Sarah Chester, Christina Mauser, John Altobelli, Keri Altobelli, Alyssa Altobelli and pilot Ara Zobayan.



In my story, my chopper did not crash, but my marriage life did, my children's path, my mother, my sisters, friends whom believed in me, my agent, my uncle Andy Johnson (Golden State Warrior) as my murderers live on.



My killers are human helicopters, who error ed greatly, tried to hide them by putting the onuis of truth in the garbage can literally.



They live on without penalty or having to own up to there mistakes, that have altered my life course and my children and family.



B'H' But I put my trust in Job Iyov 24:24 Ketuvim....



For one can be killed mentally, which for those acquainted with subatomic quantum physics understand. For sense experiences in the material world, can carry the same weight as those absent, except, one may still be in the body, but life can become a walking tragedy although alive.

A corpse or zombie, full of pain, defeat, dead, depression, you lose your life, as it becomes a repeated nightmare, as your childhood, like Gigi, is destroyed by metal, fire and the impact of negativity and unethically dealings.......



This hit me hard, it touched a chord that brought up old wounds, as I see the faces of so many people, players who were suppose to be my friends and networks. I see what was suppose to possibly me my city, where an invitation to the Warriors camp was avoided me, due to the men who killed me and destroyed my dream, in order to intentionally, make sure my NBA opportunity, even with another franchise would avoid me.



I died too, but I'am still alive, as I feel Kobe, Gigi and all the others are also still alive, but operating on a frequency, unlearned in the natural.



I got the message and the lesson, and I will not name names for now, unless, time directs me to that. Believe me, my death and resurrection due to an insurrection against my person, my constitution as a human being, that which is the cause of that which is my governance, my humanity, will be vindicated.



At the same time, my story may give life and rise to other basketball NBA prospects, wrongfully passed over, abused, cut because of back door deals, agent cliches, secret commissions, union pressure, lies and organized crime ties and favors.



Brute talent and outright genius can be passed over in any field, any government, any corporation, any family, when we allow ignorance to operate without a moral compass, without integrity, with malice, arrogance possessing little or no ethics.



Daniel Moshe Johnson



danielmoshejohnson@aol.com

snippet.textDisplay: I feel so bad for her and for all the families who lost their love ones. I could not stop crying during the speech. I was pretty sad weeks before the celebration at staples center. The accident was very close to my house. I have been trying to focus on Kobe's speeches to deal with this and amazingly I am trying to practice the mamba mentality. I am sure this would make him happy as I was never a sport person but indeed in all aspects of life even if you are not in sports is such a philosophy for all of us to learn. He was definitely a legend and Gigi was going to be another one. For her 13 years she got there. RIP K@G we will love you for ever. I wish I could meet their family in person but all my prayers and love go to you all. Hugs Clara
